latestPosts.caption: Satin skirts are a total vibe! If you're looking to add some femininity and romance to your wardrobe, look no further. With a plethora of colors to choose from, you can easily find one that matches your unique style. As someone who values creativity, softness, and a touch of romance, I can confidently say that these skirts are a staple in my wardrobe. The key is to wear what truly represents you!

Scarf can be a cute top.. and this is absolutely simple way of styling!

Outfit recreation alert! I took inspiration from Myntra and revamped my kurta into a high-low style, plus made a dhoti out of my dupatta. Super happy with the result! Would you attempt a similar transformation?

One of my lovely followers asked me to recreate a drape, and I'm excited to share my attempt! The original was a bit fast-paced, so I had to watch it a few times to grasp the process. I used a plain saree, just like Tia Bhuva, but please keep in mind that my version might look different due to embroidered border. 
Living in the Philippines, my Indian saree and dupatta collection is limited, so I get creative with what I have. I hope you enjoy my fashion endeavors, and please bear with my constraints!

latestPosts.caption:
GRWM 

Today, I'm trying out the popular denim on denim trend.. 

A tip when purchasing denim: deeper or lighter shades tend to look more luxurious. Other colors can appear less sophisticated. 

Denim and white is timeless, but I've played around with the silhouette. I've worn a bubble cropped top with pleated denim shorts and a denim blazer.. 

Finished the look with flower sandals and a white sling. I replaced the bag's belt with a pearl one. Send me a message if you'd like the link..
